    <div class="project-grid">

      <section class="project-section">
        <h2>Project Overview</h2>
        <p>The Martens Beton project was a product animation created to introduce the Qube — a new line of concrete sewer pipes featuring an innovative rolling ring system. Unlike traditional pipe assemblies that require lubrication to join sections together, the Qube's rolling ring allows pipes to be connected cleanly and easily without any lubricant. The deliverable was a short explanatory animation that walks the viewer through how the product works, guiding them step by step through the assembly process to clearly communicate the advantage of the new design.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="project-section">
        <h2>Client &amp; Context</h2>
        <p>Martens Beton is a manufacturer of concrete products based in the Netherlands. They approached Enversed Studios to create a product launch video for the Qube line that could be used in sales and marketing contexts. The goal was to explain a fairly technical innovation — the rolling ring mechanism — in a visual and accessible way, without requiring any prior knowledge of pipe systems from the viewer.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="project-section">
        <h2>Goals &amp; Challenges</h2>
        <p>The main objective was to produce a clear, visually clean animation that made the product's key selling point immediately understandable. The biggest challenge on this project was not a technical one but a process one: the revision cycle. Despite being a relatively short and contained animation, the number of feedback rounds was extensive, requiring large sections to be re-rendered repeatedly. This caused the project to run considerably longer than the scope suggested it should.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="project-section">
        <h2>Technical Details</h2>
        <p>The animation was built entirely in Blender, covering everything from modelling the pipe geometry and ring components to setting up the mechanical assembly sequence and camera work. Post-production and final compositing were done in After Effects, where the timing, titles, and any graphic overlays were added to create the finished video.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="project-section">
        <h2>Reflection</h2>
        <p>The biggest takeaway from Martens Beton was the importance of maintaining a clean and well-structured project file from the very first day — even on small, seemingly simple projects. When revisions keep coming in and files get patched and updated repeatedly, a messy project structure turns what should be a quick fix into a time-consuming rebuild. Starting clean and staying organised is the only way to stay agile through an unpredictable feedback process.</p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>

</Layout>
